      <h1>Frodo Baggins</h1>
      <div class="about-page">
        <div class="image">
          <img src="/images/frodo.png" alt="Frodo" class="frodo-image" />
        </div>

        <div class="about">
          <h3>Biography:</h3>
          <p>
            Frodo Baggins, son of Drogo Baggins, was a hobbit of the Shire in
            the late Third Age. A member of the Fellowship of the Ring, he bore
            the One Ring to Mount Doom, where it was destroyed. A ring bearer,
            best friend to his gardener, Samwise Gamgee, and one of three
            hobbits who sailed from Middle-earth to the Uttermost West at the
            end of the Third Age.
          </p>
          <h3>Titles:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Bearer of the One Ring</li>
            <li>Elf-friend</li>
            <li>Deputy Mayor of the Shire</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Quotes:</h3>
          <p>
            "I will take the ring to Mordor. Although I don't know the way."
            Frodo, shouted over the confusion in the meeting to decide the fate
            of the One Ring.
          </p>
          <p>
            "Frodo wouldn't have gotten far without Sam, would he?" Frodo to
            Sam, his best friend and companion throughout the entire journey to
            Mount Doom.
          </p>
          <p>
            "There is no real going back" Frodo, when he realizes that the
            trauma and the things he has seen on his journey are too much for
            him to lead a normal life.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
